				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Paying Employees After a Fire</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-07-09T16:46:51+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">July 9, 2014 12:46 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">July 9, 2014 12:46 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/07/09/today-in-small-business-paying-employees-after-a-fire/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Paying Employees After a Fire" data-description="Optimism falls. Potato-salad copycats emerge on Kickstarter. And approval rates at big banks hit a post-recession high.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Small-business <a href="//www.latimes.com/business/money/la-fi-small-business-optimism-nfib-economy-20140708-story.html">optimism drops</a> despite upbeat hiring plans.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ May job <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/economy-policy/2014/07/08/may-job-openings-rise-to-464-million/">openings rise</a> to 4.64 million.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A restaurant owner pays his employees <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/235479">$144,000 out of his own pocket</a> while his fire-damaged restaurant is re-built.</p>
